1
00:00:03,710 --> 00:00:07,751
Rūpa Gosvāmī’s poetry
is so beautiful and sometimes 
 

2
00:00:07,751 --> 00:00:10,926
with Śrīla Guru Mahārāj’s writings 
is also compared.

3
00:00:10,926 --> 00:00:14,522
[Ontological Substance and Poetic Beauty]

4
00:00:14,522 --> 00:00:18,001
Because you have ontology.
 

5
00:00:18,001 --> 00:00:20,031
This is what 
Śrīla Keshava Mahārāj said.

6
00:00:20,031 --> 00:00:24,014
Śrīla Bhakti Prajñān Keśava Mahārāj.

7
00:00:24,014 --> 00:00:26,039
He took sannyās from 
Śrīla Guru Mahārāj

8
00:00:26,039 --> 00:00:30,480
and gave sannyās to
Śrīla Swāmī Mahārāj Prabhupād.

9
00:00:30,480 --> 00:00:35,018
When he heard 
the Prema Dhama Deva Stotram,

10
00:00:35,018 --> 00:00:40,918
with joy, he said,
“No one can compete with him.

11
00:00:40,918 --> 00:00:46,758
It because we find here 
this perfect combination

12
00:00:46,758 --> 00:00:52,872
of ontological substance, 
and poetic beauty.

13
00:00:52,872 --> 00:01:00,731
Sometimes the substance is there, 
but the language is not so nice,

14
00:01:00,733 --> 00:01:07,424
or, I mean not so nice in the sense
of the poetic sense.

15
00:01:07,478 --> 00:01:14,962
Other times the poetry, 
the style is very charming,

16
00:01:14,989 --> 00:01:18,556
but the substance
isn’t there.

17
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:24,219
So, of the two, we can tolerate
when the substance is there,

18
00:01:24,229 --> 00:01:26,550
and maybe the language
is a little stilted

19
00:01:26,550 --> 00:01:32,650
or it’s not
the most charming flow.

20
00:01:32,790 --> 00:01:34,543
I mean I don’t want
to speak in any way 
 

21
00:01:34,543 --> 00:01:38,233
to comet offence;
one of the offences

22
00:01:38,233 --> 00:01:41,031
to the Holy Name—
blasphemy the Scriptures,

23
00:01:41,031 --> 00:01:43,754
But in a sweet way, 
Śrīla Gurudev said,

24
00:01:43,781 --> 00:01:45,919
“Some of the things 
Vedavyās has written,

25
00:01:45,919 --> 00:01:48,179
we hear the grandeur
of the ślokas like

26
00:01:48,179 --> 00:02:00,384
janmādy asya yato ’nvayād itarataś cārtheṣv abhijñaḥ svarāṭ
tene brahma hṛdā ya ādi-kavaye muhyanti yat sūrayaḥ
 

27
00:02:00,384 --> 00:02:11,470
tejo-vāri-mṛdāṁ yathā vinimayo yatra tri-sargo ’mṛṣā
dhāmnā svena sadā nirasta-kuhakaṁ satyaṁ paraṁ dhīmahi
[SB: 1.1.1]”

28
00:02:11,660 --> 00:02:14,115
That is beautiful,
but Gurudev said,

29
00:02:14,115 --> 00:02:19,415
“That is like the dance of elephants.”
Like, you are astonished

30
00:02:19,415 --> 00:02:22,301
but you don’t want 
to come too close.

31
00:02:22,301 --> 00:02:25,681
You want to watch from a far
the dance of the elephants.

32
00:02:25,681 --> 00:02:35,781
It’s not so inviting, but 
that majestic rhythm there.

33
00:02:35,789 --> 00:02:39,969
He said, “Whereas when Vedavyās,
(and it’s composed by Vedavyās)

34
00:02:40,018 --> 00:02:43,602
when he comes 
to the gopī-gita,

35
00:02:43,602 --> 00:02:49,632
the gopī-gita in the 10th Canto
of Śrīmad-Bhāgavatam.

36
00:02:49,632 --> 00:02:54,551
When these expressions come
from the Vraja-gopīs,

37
00:02:54,551 --> 00:02:57,996
then it’s very sweet, the meter changes
and we have

38
00:02:57,996 --> 00:03:04,500
tava kathāmṛtaṁ tapta-jīvanaṁ
kavibhir īḍitaṁ kalmaṣāpaham

39
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:11,500
śravaṇa-maṅgalaṁ śrīmad ātataṁ
bhuvi gṛṇanti ye bhūri-dā janāḥ [SB: 10.31.9]

40
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:19,413
So this tava kathāmṛtaṁ ta …
ta-va-ka-tha-am-rtam ta …

41
00:03:19,413 --> 00:03:22,861
The first and the seventh rhyme,
and there is other internal rhyme.

42
00:03:22,861 --> 00:03:29,351
Very … the alankar—the poetic
ornamentation is there,

43
00:03:29,351 --> 00:03:33,704
and also 
the ontological substance.

44
00:03:33,704 --> 00:03:43,004
So, when Śrīla Keśava Mahārāj 
gave this praise to Śrīla Guru Mahārāj.

45
00:03:43,004 --> 00:03:53,464
papa-tapa-dava-daha-dagdha-duhkha-khanditam
krsna-nama-sidhu-dhama-dhanya-dana-sagaram

46
00:03:53,464 --> 00:03:58,202
prema-dhama-devam eva naumi gaura-sundaram

47
00:03:58,202 --> 00:04:02,792
or the pranamami sada prabhupada-padam

48
00:04:03,708 --> 00:04:10,945
sujanarbuda-radhita-pada-yugam
(means ‘on yugam’)
 

49
00:04:10,945 --> 00:04:14,305
yuga-dharma-dhurandhara-patra-varam

50
00:04:14,305 --> 00:04:22,307
varadabhaya-dayaka-pujya-padam
pranamami sada prabhupada-padam

51
00:04:22,307 --> 00:04:27,287
guna mañjari garima guna hari vasana vayanam

52
00:04:27,413 --> 00:04:31,683
very sweet, but 
the substance is there.

53
00:04:32,104 --> 00:04:40,574
svarna-koti-darpanabha-deha-varna-gauravam
padma-parijata-gandha-vanditanga-saurabham

54
00:04:40,958 --> 00:04:48,562
koti-kama-murcchitanghri-rupa-rasa-rangaram
prema-dhama-devam eva naumi gaura-sundaram

55
00:04:48,562 --> 00:04:51,562
Hearing these type of ślokas, 
Keśava Mahārāj said,

56
00:04:51,562 --> 00:04:56,812
“No one can compete with him,
there is no contest.”

57
00:04:56,870 --> 00:04:59,390
I mean that’s 
spiritual substance

58
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:02,470
and the beauty,
the poetic beauty.

